name: r-testthat
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "3.1.4" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-testthat
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/testthat_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/testthat/testthat_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: a47eec031b4e186a8bd331031371b2347063a283050eca2adbfaa37d7a6c9c09

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - cross-r-base {{ r_base }}  # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-rlang >=0.4.1            # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-magrittr                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - r-brio                     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-r6 >=2.2.0
    - r-brio
    - r-callr >=3.5.1
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon >=1.3.4
    - r-desc
    - r-digest
    - r-ellipsis >=0.2.0
    - r-evaluate
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pkgload
    - r-praise
    - r-processx
    - r-ps >=1.3.4
    - r-rlang >=0.4.1
    - r-waldo >=0.2.1
    - r-withr >=2.0.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-r6 >=2.2.0
    - r-brio
    - r-callr >=3.5.1
    - r-cli
    - r-crayon >=1.3.4
    - r-desc
    - r-digest
    - r-ellipsis >=0.2.0
    - r-evaluate
    - r-jsonlite
    - r-lifecycle
    - r-magrittr
    - r-pkgload
    - r-praise
    - r-processx
    - r-ps >=1.3.4
    - r-rlang >=0.4.1
    - r-waldo >=0.2.1
    - r-withr >=2.0.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('testthat')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('testthat')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: http://testthat.r-lib.org, https://github.com/r-lib/testthat
  license: MIT
  summary: Software testing is important, but, in part because it is frustrating and boring, many of us avoid it. 'testthat' is a testing framework for R that is easy to learn and use, and integrates with your existing 'workflow'.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
